********************************************************************************
SOFTWARE DEPENDENCIES
********************************************************************************
- Python 2.6.x or newer (except Python 3)
	Download from here: http://www.python.org/getit/
	
- LibSVM
	Download from here: http://www.csie.ntu.edu.tw/~cjlin/libsvm/
	Plase remember to install the Python bindings.
	
- NumPy
	Download from here: http://sourceforge.net/projects/numpy/files/
	
- SciPy
	Download from here: http://sourceforge.net/projects/scipy/files/
	
Please note that most recent Linux distributions, comes with Python previously
installed.
Since Ubuntu 10.04 all this software is available from Synaptic.

********************************************************************************
USAGE
********************************************************************************

fea_vec, fea_val = feature_smc1(I,I_p)

Input : (1) I: reference image
		(2) I_p: distorted image

Output: 256 dimensional feature vector for further processing with machine
		learning technique like SVR
